Scores and Menus:
- Added main menu

- Added speed & health upgrade system
- Added auto-saving as well as upgrades, scores, and coins saving

Player Classes:

- Buffs Added

- Post Proccessing
- Stage Change Color Tinting

- Font Size Changes

MASSIVE Back-End Changes:
- HUGE code overhaul to new version
- Dropped support for all older versions

Combat Changes:
- Changed range modifiers a bit for balancing
- Made sword attack up to 3 enemies at once
- Edited player acceleration to feel much more snappy

Bats & Spellcasters:
- Added new enemy: Bat (fast movement speed, minimal damage, easy to take down)
- Added new enemy: Spellcaster (does not move, points and shoots spells at you, easy to take down, long range attack)
- Nerfed Spellcasters

Consumables:
- Edited Health Potions
- Edited Rage Potions
- Added Health Boost Potions
- Added Shields
- Added Ancient Relics (not exactly a consumable but eh)

Visual Changes:
- Enhanced kill effect for more blood
- Edited spray for kill

Level Changes:
- Removed 2 Levels
- Added 2 wave-system levels (spiders come in waves)
- Added 1 timed level (reach the end in time..or else)
- Added some chests in certain places, edited chest despawn times, and changed items of chests
- Added random item chests
- Added more npcs
- Added stage system

Bugfixes: 
- Fixed the level 7 bug with infinite heal potions
- Fixed Old Soldier
- Fixed lots of font issues
- Fixed space key + mouse click spam fixes
- Fixed "click anywhere to clos"
- Fixed health bar size issues
- I cannot tell you how many fucking bugs there were with the main menu that I had to fix, the amount would be over 20 taking up a total of 4 fucking hours to debug the shit out of.

Optimizations:
- Optimized all guis to use new UI rendering system
- Optimized particles more with spritesheet pre-rendering
- Optimized game map rendering
- Optimized localstorage usage
- Optimized Bullet & SmallMeal collisions

Meal Dungeon update version 5 is the biggest update yet! With main menu changes, updated code, visuals, scores, upgrades, characters/classes, consumables, stage systems, new levels, combat changes, and loads of bugfixes, meal dungeon v5 makes playing the game over and over actually fun!
